## Examples

### Creating a Pull Request

```bash
# Create a PR from the current branch
gh pr create

# Create a PR with title and body
gh pr create --title "Fix login bug" --body "This PR fixes the login issue"

# Create a draft PR
gh pr create --draft
```

### Working with Issues

```bash
# List open issues assigned to you
gh issue list --assignee @me

# Create an issue
gh issue create --title "New feature request" --body "Please add this feature"

# Close an issue with a comment
gh issue close 123 --comment "Fixed in PR #456"
```

### Repository Operations

```bash
# Clone a repository
gh repo clone owner/repo

# Create a new repository
gh repo create my-project --public

# View repository details
gh repo view owner/repo
```

### GitHub Actions

```bash
# List recent workflow runs
gh run list

# Watch a workflow run in progress
gh run watch

# Manually trigger a workflow
gh workflow run workflow-name.yml
```

## Advanced Usage

### Using with Git Aliases

```bash
git config --global alias.pr 'gh pr create'
```

### Writing Scripts

```bash
# Get the URL of the current repository
repo_url=$(gh repo view --json url -q .url)

# List all pull requests and extract numbers
pr_numbers=$(gh pr list --json number -q '.[].number')
```

### Environment Variables

- `GH_TOKEN`: Authentication token
- `GH_HOST`: GitHub hostname for GitHub Enterprise
- `GH_REPO`: Repository in OWNER/REPO format
- `GH_EDITOR`: Editor to use for authoring
- `GH_BROWSER`: Browser to use for web content